subSubSection.paragraph:
Pelagic species preferring close proximity to substrate and seeking out slacker areas such as backwater, eddies and pools below riffles. Occurs in shoals and prefers well-aerated, open water in flowing rivers (
Skelton 2001
), favouring the upper stratum (
Engelbrecht and Mulder 1999
). Feeds from water column on planktonic crustaceans and insects (e.g. midges and ants) (
Skelton 2001
). Caught at night with light. Breeding occurs in early summer (
Skelton 2001
). Found in dams where appears to propagate successfully with little predation and moves around in rivers according to seasonal flows. Appears to migrate up streams in spring to breed where it is found in tributaries.
